\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. F. pyrenaica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 304 (1753). Stem 15-30 cm. Leaves 7-10, alternate, the lowest 4·5-11 cm × 6-10 mm, obtuse, the rest narrower, usually acute. Perianth broadly campanulate, usually expanded at the mouth; segments dark purplish-brown and usually without fascia outside, greenish-yellow and tessellated with brown inside, the outer 25-35 × 7-10 mm, acute, the inner 10-15 mm wide, obtuse or apiculate. Nectaries 4-6 mm × 2-4 mm at base, triangular to ovate-lanceolate. Filaments 9 mm, papillose. Style 8-9 mm, 3-fid, the branches 2-4 mm, slender, smooth. Capsule not winged.{\i  Mountain meadows. • From S.C. France to N.W. Spain.} Ga Hs.
\par

