\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. F. lusitanica} Wikström,{\i  Kungl. Svenska Vet.-Acad. Handl.}{\b  1821}: 352 (1821) (incl.{\i  F. hispanica} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i F. stenophylla} Boiss. & Reuter,{\i  F. boissieri} Costa, {\i F. messanensis} sensu Willk., non Rafin.). Stem 10-50 cm. Leaves (5-)6-9(-11), alternate, the lowest 4·8-7·5(-15) cm × 1-9 mm, linear to lanceolate, the rest narrower. Flowers 1(-3). Perianth broadly campanulate, often expanded at the mouth; segments green to brown outside, usually with green fascia, yellowish inside, marked or tessellated with brown, the outer 20-40 × 7-10 mm, the inner 9-15 mm wide, usually acute. Nectaries 10-12 × 2-3 mm, linear-lanceolate to linear, greenish, 3-4 mm above the base of the perianth-segment. Filaments 8-10 mm. Style 8-11 mm, 3-fid, the branches 3-4 mm, slender, smooth. Capsule not winged. 2n = 24.{\i  Rocks, screes and open woods. • E., C. & S. Spain, C. & S. Portugal}. Hs Lu.
