\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. F. ruthenica} Wikström,{\i  op. cit.} 353 (1821) ({\i F. minor} Ledeb.). Stem 20-50 cm. Leaves 6-12, linear, opposite or in whorls of 3, the uppermost often on an extension of the stem above the flowers, the lowest 6-9 cm × 3-5 mm, the uppermost with filiform, tendril-like apex. Flowers 1-5, in a lax raceme. Perianth broadly campanulate; segments acute, blackish outside, greenish-yellow inside, tessellated with purplish-brown, the outer c. 25 × 7 mm, the inner c. 10 mm wide. Nectaries 10-14 mm, linear, c. 4 mm above the base of the perianth-segment. Filaments c. 10 mm, papillose. Style c. 9 mm, 3-fid, the branches 2 mm, papillose. Capsule winged.{\i  S. & S.E. parts of U.S.S.R.} Rs (C, W, E).
