\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. F. orientalis} Adams in Weber fil. & Mohr,{\i  Beitr. Naturk.}{\b  1}: 50 (1805) ({\i F. tenella} Bieb., {\i F. montana} Hoppe). Stem 16-40 cm. Leaves (6-)8-10(-11), the lowest 4-13 cm × 3-6(-10) mm, linear, usually opposite or in a whorl of 3, the intermediate alternate, the uppermost 2·5-5(-11) cm, usually in a whorl of 3, the apex often curved or hooked, but not filiform or tendril-like. Perianth broadly campanulate; segments greenish, heavily tessellated inside and outside with purplish-brown, the outer 20-30(-35) × 6-10 mm, the inner 9-13 mm wide. Nectaries 10-15 × 2 mm, greenish, linear, 5 mm above the base of the perianth-segment. Filaments 8 mm, papillose. Capsule not winged. Style 8-10 mm, 3-fid, the branches 2-7 mm, papillose. 2n = 18+0-9B.{\i  S. & S.E. Europe, westwards to S.E. France.} Al Bu Ga Gr It Ju Rm Rs (W).
