\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. F. drenovskii} Degen & Stoj., {\i Bull. Inst. Roy. Hist. Nat.} ({\i Sofia}){\b  4}: 142 (1931). Stem 17-30 cm. Leaves 4-5(-9), alternate, the lowest 6-7(-14) cm × 4-6 mm, linear-lanceolate, the rest narrower. Flowers 1(-3). Perianth narrowly campanulate; segments dark purplish to reddish-brown, glaucous outside, yellowish-green inside, the outer 16-25 × 4-8 mm, acute, the inner 5-11 mm wide, acute or obtuse. Nectaries 2 × 1 mm, at the base of the perianth-segment, green. Filaments 8-9 mm, papillose. Style 8-10 mm, 3-fid, the branches 1 mm, papillose. Capsule not winged. • {\i N.E. Greece, S.W. Bulgaria.} Bu Gr.
